des: "This is super easy, something different and tastes great with the main course. Enjoy! Originally submitted to ThanksgivingRecipe.com."
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
Combine the pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, melted butter and ground cinnamon to taste. Spoon into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 1 hour.
